14. Nxc6 bxc6! {[%cal Ga8b8,Rd6h2,Rc7h2][%csl Rh2,Rb2]} { Opening the c-file would be detrimental with the rook already on c1, but recapturing with the pawn is very decent. Our structure is worse, but we enjoy some strong counterplay along the b-file and the h2-c7 diagonal. } 
