However, while the drawing margin seems pretty big, our winning chances are also considerably lower than in our line, and therefore, I consider it too pessimistic a choice. } ) 
14. Qd4 { The only move, as White really needs to pick up a pawn to compensate for our strong bishops. } Qxd7! 
15. Qxh8 { Too greedy, but important to know. } Qd2+ 
16. Kf1 Qxb2 
17. Re1 { Only move not to lose instantly. } Bb4 
18. Qe5 Be6 {[%csl Rc3,Rf1]} { This is just winning - we pick up c3 and break through on the 1st rank afterwards. } 
