Better is } ) ( 21.Rd1 Nec4 { Intending the cute tactical trick ...Ba3. } 22.Ne4 { White's point is to meet } 22...Ba3 { with } 23.Qc3 { , easing up on the pressure. Instead, @@StartFEN@@1k5r/pp3p2/1np5/q1b2N2/P1n1N3/6P1/1PQ1PPB1/1K1R4 b - - 3 22@@EndFEN@@ 22...Qb4 threatening ...Na3+, as well as the more prosaic ...Nxa4, when White does well to bail out into an equal ending: 23.Qc3! Qxc3 24.bxc3 Nxa4 . A rather strange pawn structure has arisen. It’s hard to say exactly who this favors. White’s pawns are probably slightly stronger, but on the other hand, our king is still the safer one. Most probably, the limited material makes the position rather drawish, although there is still a lot to play for. } )
