22.-- ( { Slightly accurate, to gain a tempo on the rook on d4 later on. Now the game will steer towards a draw rather quickly, but we should still show a little bit of accuracy in order not to collapse on the light squares: } 22.Bxd4 { White has nothing else. } 22...exd4 23.Rxd4 Bc5 { Trying to gain a tempo for ...Rad8. } 24.Nxf6+ gxf6 25.Rd7 { This is the annoying thing. The rook can settle on the 7th rank before we've had a chance to play ...Rad8. } 25...Qb6 { Defending b7 while putting some annoying pressure on f2. } 26.Bc4 Qc6 { Not allowing a5 with tempo. } 27.Rad1 Kg7 { The last key move. Next, we are ready for ...Rae8 followed by ...Re7, after which we are completely safe. We need ...Kg7 in order not to allow any Bxf7+ tricks. White should probably already now look for bailouts, as otherwise, their weakened king could become an issue later on. } )
