9. e5 h6 
10. Bh4 g5 
11. Bg3 ( 11.Nxg5? { The Botvinnik move, but here it doesn't work at all. } 11...hxg5 12.Bxg5 Qc7 { Whoops. Now White can't take on f6 due to checkmate on h2! } ) Nh5! {[%cal Ga7a6,Gf8e7,Yh5g3]} { Making sure to collect the bishop on g3. White has a certain amount of compensation, similar to the Anti-Moscow Semi-Slav, but our play is not that difficult. We play ...a6, ...Be7, and then both long and short castles are viable options. Care is needed, but objectively White is not equalizing. } 
