8. e5 {[%mdl 32768]} { A straightforward move, but similar to the old Geller Gambit [/variation/22637569/#/6/w] it's not quite flexible or subtle enough. } Nd5 
9. Ne4 { Here there are many reasonable ways of playing, but for simplicity’s sake, I prefer to play in the same way as with a4 a6 included. } h6!? {[%cal Rc1g5]} { Preventing Bg5. } 
10. Bd2 a5 { Exactly the same [/variation/22637581/#/11/b] as with a4 a6 included, and for the same reasons! } 
11. b3 cxb3 
12. axb3 { This is the extra option White gets by not including a4 a6, but it shouldn't be enough to worry us. } Nd7 {[%cal Gf8e7,Ge8g8,Yb5b4,Yc6c5]} { Followed by ...Be7 and ...O-O. Long term, we intend to play ...b4 and push ...c5 through. } 
