8. Bxc4 Bb7 
9. O-O Nbd7 {[%cal Gf8e7,Ge7d6,Ge8g8,Yc6c5][%csl Ra2]} { Continuing with our development. We will play either ...Be7 or ...Bd6, ...O-O, and then push ...c5 at an appropriate moment. With the knight offside on a2, White can't push e4, and without that, there aren't that many good plans available.

Compared to, for instance, the Queen's Gambit Accepted, we have a dream version, and the play should be rather straightforward from here. } 
