12. Nxg6 hxg6 
13. Nxd5 exd5 { Trading the extra set of knights is beneficial for us. As a rule of thumb, it's always better to trade the other knight when playing against the bishop pair, as then the two knights won't fight for the same squares. Here we also get the useful possibility of ...Bb4 later on to trade the dark-squared bishop. } 
14. Qxd5?? { Falling into our trap! } Rxh2 
15. Rxh2 { If we now simply recapture the rook, White is better, as the d5-pawn is more valuable than the one on h2. } Qg3+ {[%cal Gc6d5][%csl Re1]} { Winning the queen and the game! } 
