9. e4 { Nothing else makes any sense. } dxe4 
10. Ndxe4 Nxe4 { Trading more pieces makes sense, as every trade makes the white d-pawn slightly weaker. } 
11. Nxe4 Nf6 { Immediately challenging the e4-knight. } 
12. Nc3 { The most natural move. White gets ready to push d5. We should not be too worried, though - the main thing that will happen after d5 is that most pieces will get traded off, with an equal game. } Qb6!? { This is why I recommend starting with @@StartFEN@@rn1qk2r/pp2bpp1/2p1pn1p/3p1b2/2PP4/2N3P1/PP1NPPBP/R1BQ1RK1 b kq - 3 8@@EndFEN@@ 8...Nbd7 rather than 8...O-O . We are one move faster with putting pressure on the d-pawn. } 
