10. Bf1 {[%mdl 32768]} { Another typical move for such situations, but it doesn't change much. } Nbd7 { Again, as soon as White slows down the game (either by castling short or, like here, spending two moves with the bishop), we can safely continue with the most natural plan. } 
11. Bg2 Nb6 
12. O-O Re8 { Very similar to Yilmaz-Durarbayli. [/variation/22638422/#/13/b] White can try to come up with a more useful move than Re1, but I don't really see it. } 
