However, one of the main advantages of the system I recommend is that we are hard to trick move order-wise. We can usually play the same moves no matter what White does. } Nf6 
5. Bg5 { This is usually not a great square for the bishop in the Slav, and this is not an exception. But it is important to know how to handle it. } Ne4 { We should never allow doubled f-pawns. } 
6. Nxe4 ( 6.Bf4 Nc6 { is perfectly healthy. } ) dxe4 
