14. Rfc1 O-O {[%cal Rd6e5]} { Getting the king into safety. Now we are ready to eliminate the e5-knight next. } 
15. Bxf6 { The only critical move. White ruins our structure, but as mentioned previously, we also get play along the g-file. } gxf6 
16. Nf3! { Keeping the knight as a defender of the king. } Kh8 {[%cal Gf8g8]} { Not strictly necessary, as playing the usual way with ...Rfc8, etc. is also solid. But I feel that once we have allowed the doubled f-pawns, we should do our utmost to exploit its upsides, i.e., playing on the g-file.

Practically speaking, I believe we have excellent counterplay, but it involves some risk - White will be slightly better if they manage to defend their king. } 
