8. Bg3 Be7 { If we can finish development undisturbed, we will now just be better. } 
9. Bb5 { The only move to disturb us. } a6! { Forcing the issue. } 
10. Bxd7+ Bxd7 
11. Bxe5 { Forced, as otherwise, we would have a strong bishop pair for free. } b6! {[%cal Rb6c5,Re7b4]} { It's important that we do this before castling, as now the b4-pawn is hanging with check. It looks a bit loose with g7 also hanging, but the main point is that the position becomes open, favoring our bishops. } 
12. Ne2 ( 12.Bxg7 Rg8 { followed by ...Rxg2 only helps us. } ) bxc5 
13. bxc5 O-O 
