1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} d5 
2. c4 c6 { Let's revisit some ideas, plans, and pawn structures studied throughout the course using some interesting positions taken from tournament practice!

In Exercises 1-5, you'll need to find the best continuation for Black to execute our plan, pressure the opponent, or neutralize White's intentions.

Finally, in Exercise 6, I'll ask you to take the white pieces and come up with a way to pose problems. When we play, we should be aware of our opponent's plans instead of just focusing on our own. :-)

I hope these exercises are enjoyable and valuable to you! } 
