27. Bxa6? {[%mdl 32768]} { It looks good for White as the c6-knight is hanging, but there is a hidden resource! } { We have a fairly equal Exchange Slav, but White's structure is slightly weaker, especially as the pawns on b3 and a2 can be attacked by the queen + knight combo. With normal play, White would have to suffer a bit, and therefore he decided to complicate matters. Is 27.Bxa6 a good or a bad move? } g5! {[%csl Rd4,Re3]} { Surprisingly, there is no good way for White to hold onto the center any longer! } 
28. g3 ( 28.fxg5 Qd6+ { followed by ...bxa6 is the big tactical point. The bishop is lost. } ) gxf4 
29. exf4 {[%csl Rd4]} ( { The best try, but now d4 is lost. } 29.gxf4 g5! { works in the same way, but an even better version. Once the d4-pawn falls, the center collapses. } ) g6 {[%cal Gf8g7]} { This was the simplest way to continue. Black hides the king on g7 and picks up the d4-pawn, with a great edge. } 
